The awards ceremony aired for a period of five days and for the first time in history there was no live audience. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Songstress, Ami Faku, has walked away with the Best Female of the Year award at the 26th South African Music Awards. This is Faku's first award at the SAMAs. The awards ceremony aired for a period of five days and for the first time in history there was no live audience. Ami Faku was up against Lay Zamar, Riana Nel, Spha Mdlalose and Manu Grace. 